article.description:
Omar Thomas scored 21 points and Filiberto Rivera added 19 to help UTEP beat Hawaii 80-62 in the quarterfinals
of the Western Athletic Conference tournament on Thursday in Reno, Nev.
article.headline: Miners meet Rice in Friday's semifinal
article.linkText: UTEP puts down Hawaii in WAC quarters
article.story: HONOLULU (AP) -- Matthew Gipson had 18 points and was one of six players in double figures as Hawaii defeated Hawaii-Hilo 110-55 in an exhibition game on Friday night. Ahmet Gueye, a transfer from Salt Lake Community College in Utah, had 16 points, nine rebounds and five blocks. Teammates Matt Gibson and Julian Sensley each added 14 points for the Rainbow Warriors. Sensley also had seven rebounds and five assists. Hawaii never trailed in the game and jumped out to a 63-23 lead at the half. Justin Griffin scored 20 points to lead the Vulcans whose bench was outscored 50-15. He was the only Vulcan in double digits. Hawaii opens the season at home on Nov. 19 against fourth-ranked Michigan State. Hawaii-Hilo faces Cal State Chico on Tuesday.
